org.apache.ignite.internal.processors.cache

Class GridCacheDefaultAffinityKeyMapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.ignite.internal.processors.cache.GridCacheDefaultAffinityKeyMapper
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, AffinityKeyMapper
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CacheDefaultBinaryAffinityKeyMapper, IgfsGroupDataBlocksKeyMapper

    public class GridCacheDefaultAffinityKeyMapper
extends Object
implements AffinityKeyMapper
    Default key affinity mapper. If key class has annotation AffinityKeyMapped, then the value of annotated field will be used to get affinity value instead of the key itself. If there is no annotation, then the key is used as is.

    Convenience affinity key adapter, AffinityKey can be used in conjunction with this mapper to automatically provide custom affinity keys for cache keys.

    If non-default affinity mapper is used, is should be provided via CacheConfiguration.getAffinityMapper() configuration property.
